---
virtualenvwrapper: ! '# Virtualenvwrapper


  ## Create and start a new virtual environment


  v.mk myvirtualenv


  ## Deactivating a virtual environment


  deactivate


  ## Switch to an existing virtual environment


  v myvirtualenv


  ## List packages used by current virtual environment


  yolk -l


  ## Take a snapshot of the current environment''s packages


  pip freeze > requirements.txt


  ## Install from a snapshot


  pip install -r requirements.txt


  ## Aliases


  v=''workon''

  v.deactivate=''deactivate''

  v.mk=''mkvirtualenv --no-site-packages''

  v.mk_withsitepackages=''mkvirtualenv''

  v.rm=''rmvirtualenv''

  v.switch=''workon''

  v.add2virtualenv=''add2virtualenv''

  v.cdsitepackages=''cdsitepackages''

  v.cd=''cdvirtualenv''

  v.lssitepackages=''lssitepackages'''
